ArcelorMittal South Africa Declines to Lowest Since March 2009

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-07-27T07:08:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/arcelormittal-south-africa-drops-to-lowest-since-2009-on-earnings-forecast.html
ArcelorMittal (MT)  South Africa Ltd., a
unit of the world’s largest steelmaker, fell to its lowest
intraday level since March 2009 after saying it expects third-
quarter earnings to be “substantially lower” than the previous
three months.   Shares in the steelmaker fell as much as 5 percent to 70.50
rand, the lowest in more than two years, and traded 4.7 percent
lower at 70.70 rand as of 9:06 a.m. Johannesburg time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  